# Project Overview

This is a Qwik-based software blog web application. Here are the key files and directories:

## Entry Points
- [src/entry.cloudflare-pages.tsx](mdc:src/entry.cloudflare-pages.tsx): Main entry point for Cloudflare Pages deployment
- [src/root.tsx](mdc:src/root.tsx): Root component that sets up the blog layout and routing

## Core Configuration
- [vite.config.ts](mdc:vite.config.ts): Vite and Qwik build configuration
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json): TypeScript configuration

## Main Directories
- `src/routes`: Contains blog pages, post routes, and layouts
- `src/components`: Reusable blog components (posts, navigation)
- `src/content`: Blog posts and content management
- `public`: Static assets (images, fonts, etc.)

## Development
The project uses:
- TypeScript for type safety
- ESLint for code linting ([.eslintrc.cjs](mdc:.eslintrc.cjs))
- Prettier for code formatting ([.prettierrc.js](mdc:.prettierrc.js))
- Markdown for blog content
- @qwik-ui/headless for accessible UI components